Chains aggregation and spatial/temporal covariance computation

### This function doesn't exist anymore in the HMSC package. Let's provide a hand-made version.

## Hand-made corRandomEff() function
corRandomEff = function(hM, cor = T){
  rLevels = dim(hM$results$estimation$paramLatent)[2]
  randomMatrix = list()
  for(rL in 1:rLevels){
    randomMatrix[[rL]] = abind(hM$results$estimation$paramLatent[,rL], along = 3)
  }
  
  nSample = dim(randomMatrix[[1]])[3]
  covMatrix = list()
  for(rL in 1:rLevels){
    covMatrix[[rL]] = list()
    
    if(cor){
      for(i in 1:nSample){
        covMatrix[[rL]][[i]] = cov2cor(randomMatrix[[rL]][,,i] %*% t(randomMatrix[[rL]][,,i]))
      }
    }else{
      for(i in 1:nSample){
        covMatrix[[rL]][[i]] = randomMatrix[[rL]][,,i] %*% t(randomMatrix[[rL]][,,i])
      }
    }
    covMatrix[[rL]] = abind(covMatrix[[rL]], along = 3)
  }
  
  abind(covMatrix, along = 4)
}

corMat_ex = list()

for(i in 1:3)
  corMat_ex[[i]]<-corRandomEff(model_ex[[i]],cor=T)

# Then aggregate chains
corMat_ex = abind::abind(corMat_ex[[1]], corMat_ex[[2]], corMat_ex[[3]], along = 3)

# Then compute quantiles & "significativity"
summStats = list(ex = list(space = list(), time = list()))

for(i in 1:2){
  summStats$ex[[i]]$mean = apply(corMat_ex[,,,i],c(1:2),mean)
  summStats$ex[[i]]$median = apply(corMat_ex[,,,i],c(1:2),median)
  summStats$ex[[i]]$q025 = apply(corMat_ex[,,,i],c(1:2),quantile, probs = cutting_prob[1])
  summStats$ex[[i]]$q975 = apply(corMat_ex[,,,i],c(1:2),quantile, probs = cutting_prob[2])
}

for(i in 1:2){
  summStats$ex[[i]]$alphasized = summStats$ex[[i]]$mean
  summStats$ex[[i]]$alphasized[summStats$ex[[i]]$q025 * summStats$ex[[i]]$q975 < 0] = 0.5
  summStats$ex[[i]]$alphasized[summStats$ex[[i]]$q025 * summStats$ex[[i]]$q975 >= 0] = 1
}

# "Seriate" to find nice order
scons = names(seriate(summStats$ex$space$median)[[1]])
scons_idx = as.integer(seriate(summStats$ex$space$median)[[1]])

# Reorder matrices
for(i in 1:1){for(j in 1:2){for(k in 1:5){
  summStats[[i]][[j]][[k]] = summStats[[i]][[j]][[k]][scons_idx, scons_idx]
}}}

We want to transform effects to relative amplitudes.

Arrays have to be expand : 29 parameters by species (1:intercept, +2:12 cov (11), +13:29 species (17))

# Expand the table to include transformed cov (11) + sp effct (17) : 28 new "columns" (from 30 to 57)
for(i in 30:57){
  paramXall_ex = flodel1(paramXall_ex, 2)
}

Transform to relative amplitude for environmental effects (scaled): i.e. \(\tilde{\beta_{s, x}} = [\Phi(\mu_s+\beta_{s,x})-\Phi(\mu_s-\beta_{s,x})] / \Phi(\mu_s)\), with \(\Phi()\) the inverse probit function.

for(i in 30:40)
  paramXall_ex[,i,] = (pnorm(paramXall_ex[,1,] + paramXall_ex[,i-28,]) - pnorm(paramXall_ex[,1,] - paramXall_ex[,i-28,])) / pnorm(paramXall_ex[,1,])

Transform to relative amplitude for among species effects (un-scaled): i.e. \(\tilde{\beta_{i,j}} = [\Phi(\mu_i+\beta_{ij})-\Phi(\mu_i)] / \Phi(\mu_i)\).

for(i in 41:57)
  paramXall_ex[,i,] = (pnorm(paramXall_ex[,1,] + paramXall_ex[,i-28,]) - pnorm(paramXall_ex[,1,])) / pnorm(paramXall_ex[,1,])

summresults_fixef = list(ex = list(notrans = list(intercpt = list(),
                                                  fixEnvt = list(),

                                                fixInte = list())))

fillall = function(dat, order = NULL){
  list(mean = apply(dat, c(1,2), mean),
         median = apply(dat, c(1,2), median),
         q025 = apply(dat, c(1,2), quantile, cutting_prob[1]),
         q975 = apply(dat, c(1,2), quantile, cutting_prob[2]))
}

summresults_fixef$ex$notrans$fixEnvt = fillall(paramXall_ex[,2:12,])
summresults_fixef$ex$notrans$fixInte = fillall(paramXall_ex[,13:29,])
summresults_fixef$ex$trans$fixEnvt = fillall(paramXall_ex[,30:40,])
summresults_fixef$ex$trans$fixInte = fillall(paramXall_ex[,41:57,])

## Adding alphasized (note they are compute on the non-transformed estimates)
# for environmental effects
summresults_fixef$ex$alphasized$envt = summresults_fixef$ex$notrans$fixEnvt$median
summresults_fixef$ex$alphasized$envt[summresults_fixef$ex$notrans$fixEnvt$q025 * summresults_fixef$ex$notrans$fixEnvt$q975 < 0] = 0.5
summresults_fixef$ex$alphasized$envt[summresults_fixef$ex$notrans$fixEnvt$q025 * summresults_fixef$ex$notrans$fixEnvt$q975 >= 0] = 1
